### =============================================================================
### Exercise 4 — Status Flows
###
### Walks the Travel through its state machine using the actions annotated in
### `xstravels/srv/travel-flows.cds`:
###
###   Open ──acceptTravel──► Accepted ──reopenTravel──► Open
###     │                       ▲
###     └──rejectTravel──► Rejected ──reopenTravel──► Open
###
###   deductDiscount is only allowed while a travel is Open (guard-only,
###   does not change state).
###
### How to run:
### 1. From `xstravels/`, start `cds watch`.
### 2. Open this file in VS Code with the REST Client extension.
### 3. Send the requests in order — each block notes the expected outcome.
###
### Reading responses:
###   204 No Content → success. Bound actions like acceptTravel/rejectTravel
###     succeed without returning a body — this is the expected result, NOT
###     an error. Re-read the travel with a GET afterwards to confirm the
###     Status_code flipped.
###   409 Conflict with code INVALID_FLOW_TRANSITION_{SINGLE,MULTI} → the
###     action was called while the row was in a state not allowed by `@from`.
###
### Every request runs under user `alice` (mocked auth, has admin role).
### =============================================================================

@host      = http://localhost:4004
@service   = {{host}}/odata/v4/travel
@auth      = Basic alice:

### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Helper — find open travels (pick one with a fresh ID for the walk-through)
### -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

### List a few Open travels
GET {{service}}/Travels?$top=5&$select=ID,Status_code&$filter=Status_code eq 'O'
Authorization: {{auth}}


### =============================================================================
### Happy-path walk-through (Travel 1 by default)
### =============================================================================

### 1. Status now: Open (as seeded)
GET {{service}}/Travels(1)?$select=ID,Status_code
Authorization: {{auth}}

### 2. Deduct 10 % discount — allowed because the travel is Open
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.deductDiscount
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "percent": 10 }

### 3. Accept the travel:  Open ──► Accepted
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.acceptTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 4. Re-read status — now "A"
GET {{service}}/Travels(1)?$select=ID,Status_code
Authorization: {{auth}}

### 5. Re-open it:  Accepted ──► Open
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.reopenTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 6. Reject it:  Open ──► Rejected
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.rejectTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 7. Re-read status — now "X"
GET {{service}}/Travels(1)?$select=ID,Status_code
Authorization: {{auth}}

### 8. Re-open from Rejected:  Rejected ──► Open
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.reopenTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}


### =============================================================================
### Illegal-transition probes — each should return 409 Conflict with
### `INVALID_FLOW_TRANSITION_SINGLE` or `..._MULTI`
### =============================================================================

### First: put Travel 1 back to Accepted so the next probe has something to hit
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.acceptTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 9. ❌ acceptTravel while already Accepted → INVALID_FLOW_TRANSITION_SINGLE
###    `acceptTravel` requires Status = Open.
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.acceptTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 10. ❌ deductDiscount on a non-Open travel → INVALID_FLOW_TRANSITION_SINGLE
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.deductDiscount
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "percent": 10 }

### 11. Reset to Open, then probe reopen-on-Open
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.reopenTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 12. ❌ reopenTravel while already Open → INVALID_FLOW_TRANSITION_MULTI
###    (MULTI because reopen has two source states: [Rejected, Accepted])
POST {{service}}/Travels(ID=1,IsActiveEntity=true)/TravelService.reopenTravel
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}
